The '''yellow-rumped mannikin''' ('''''Lonchura flaviprymna''''') also known as the '''yellow-rumped munia''', is a species of [[estrildid finch]] found in the eastern [[Kimberley (Western Australia)|Kimberley region]] and north-west [[Northern Territory]], [[Australia]]. It has an estimated global extent of occurrence of 20,000 to 50,000&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup>. It is found in subtropical to tropical [[mangrove]], moist [[savanna]] and [[wetland]] habitats. The conservation status of the species is evaluated as being of [[Least Concern]].

